&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Liverpool NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Royal Liverpool Hospital &amp; Aintree Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Band 7 Specialist Nurse&lt;br /&gt;OPAT/SEPSIS Team&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liverpool NHS Foundation Trust covers the Royal Liverpool Hospital, Aintree Hospital and&lt;br /&gt;Broadgreen Hospital sites. The OPAT/SEPSIS Team are looking for an experienced person to join the team to provide specialist support and education across all Trust sites in identifying and treating patients with SEPSIS and also supporting the OPAT (outpatient IV antibiotic) patients to reduce the Length of Stay (LOS) within the Trust and facilitate early discharge for patients.&lt;br /&gt;Applicants should have good interpersonal and communication skills, having an ability to&lt;br /&gt;communicate sensitive information to patients and relatives where there may be barriers to&lt;br /&gt;communication or reassurance is required. Applicants should also be able to demonstrate&lt;br /&gt;both team work and have good organisational skills and be willing to travel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Consideration will also be given for a successful candidate via Annex 21 route to complete&lt;br /&gt;training within 12 months and this should be discussed via informal visit or interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSuzanne MarshallJob titleMatron for Infectious DiseasesAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, please contact either Suzanne Marshall, Matron (0151 706 5182)&lt;br /&gt;Suzanne.Marshall@liverpoolft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
